        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 24 at 3:34PM MDT until August 24 at 4:45PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 333 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles northeast of
Boyero, or 21 miles south of Flagler, moving south at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters on I-70.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect damage
to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

Locations impacted include...
Wild Horse and Aroya.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
